definition.value: A 3-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is butyric acid bearing a 3-oxo substituent.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose residue and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A 3-oxoacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of acetoacetic acid.
A thiol comprising a panthothenate unit in phosphoric anhydride linkage with a 3',5'-adenosine diphosphate unit; and an aminoethanethiol unit.
A D-mannofuranose in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
A methyl ketone that consists of propane bearing an oxo group at C2.
